The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as multi-target multi-camera tracking and person re-identification, which are typically studied in the computer vision subfield (cs.CV). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the machine learning subfield (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new loss function for training the neural network, which falls under the category of optimization (cs.Optimization). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which falls under the category of evaluation (cs.CR). Finally, the paper deals with multi-target tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision that deals with tracking multiple objects simultaneously (cs.MM).
